TF1 to Ask Regulator to Make LCI Free TV Channel, Echos Says

-- B y   A n d r e w   R o b e r t s
-- 
2011-07-26T05:50:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/tf1-to-ask-regulator-to-make-lci-free-tv-channel-echos-says.html
Societe Television Francaise 1 (TFI)  is
to ask France’s audiovisual regulator to allow LCI to become a
free TV channel,  Les Echos   reported , citing a person close to
the matter.  Canal+, which has exclusive distribution of TF1’s news and
information channel on ADSL and satellite, doesn’t want to pay
for LCI any more, the French newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrew Roberts in Paris at 
 aroberts36@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net . 